{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"8af96519-7be1-4ca2-92ff-6519cfdad9b8","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `*.csproj`**\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`**\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`**\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\nThen run:\n```bash\ndotnet restore\ndotnet build\n```\n\nReview the [.NET 11 breaking changes](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/core/compatibility/11.0) and update any NuGet packages (e.g. `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*`, `Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore`) to their 11.x versions.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"5a7ca74c-22f2-4aea-9cb9-8ad0d147956a","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question I can answer from knowledge — no codebase to explore. Let me provide concise guidance.","outputTokens":284,"requestId":"A469:160003:2276EB4:2636AD9:6A03D956"},"id":"0ea1b8bc-b56c-4e08-b8b5-f531f7d86c70","timestamp":"2026-05-13T01:52:27.971Z","parentId":"37e9ee87-2616-4a59-966b-1d4874fe7058"}
